The paper deals with a geometric optimization problem and introduces a novel geometric structure, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The paper also proves several nontrivial properties of the structure, which may be of independent interest in discrete geometry (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.DS). The optimization problem involves finding maximal area parallelograms, which may be related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and geometric reasoning (cs.GR). Finally, the paper mentions that the techniques developed may be useful for solving other related problems, which suggests that it may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
